[[Esther M. Friesner]]'s short story "'''That's Entertainment: The Tale of Salacious Crumb'''" appears in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'', which was published [[December]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]]. It provides the backstory for the [[Kowakian monkey-lizard/Legends|Kowakian monkey-lizard]] [[Salacious B. Crumb/Legends|Salacious B. Crumb]] and [[Melvosh Bloor]], the [[Kalkal]] professor.

==Plot summary==
An investigative [[Politics/Legends|politico]]-sociology [[Kalkal]] [[Professor/Legends|professor]], [[Melvosh Bloor]], is intent on studying the criminal underworld of [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's palace]] by attempting to interview the notorious [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]]. [[Salacious B. Crumb/Legends|Salacious B. Crumb]] appears and pretends to help Bloor. Crumb tricks Bloor into saying that [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] "lies like a [[Gran/Legends|Gran]]" along the way to Jabba's Palace. When the duo reach Jabba, Crumb explains that Bloor had said that the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] "lied like a Gran."

Jabba is tired of Crumb's idiotic jokes, and takes the interview Bloor set up. Once the professor asks how he can repay the crime lord, he tells Bloor to make him laugh. When Bloor tells the Hutt a joke he heard already, Jabba is not amused and feeds the Kalkal to the [[Rancor/Legends|rancor]].

